The earliest adventures of Miyamoto Usagi, Stan Sakai’s celebrated rabbit ronin, are available online for the first time as part of Dark Horse’s complete digital presentation of Usagi Yojimbo!

Classic Usagi Yojimbo #4 is the final collection of early Usagi short stories, including one pre-Usagi Yojimbo #1 tale and two from early in the series’ run. Gen returns in “Bounty Hunter II,” a story from Critters #14 cementing the friendship between rabbit and rhino; Usagi navigates a haunted forest in “The Tangled Skein” from Critters #38; and a fancy hairpin is the key to a ghostly mystery, in “Yurei” from Critters #50!

This collection of essential stories is the best introduction available to Stan Sakai’s enduring masterpiece!

A 'Fear Itself' chapter! Elektra and the Shroud battle the sinister Killgrave as the escaped supervillains run riot! Meanwhile, Misty Knight faces her greatest fear! By Dan Abnett, Andy Lanning and Kyle Hotz!

Veil makes a dramatic decision – and Avengers Academy changes forever! By Christos Gage and Tom Raney!

Includes material previously published in Heroes for Hire #11-12 and Avengers Academy #20.

The legacy of X-Force sends Cyclops's Extinction Team into a deadly new world! Also: an old enemy returns as the Phalanx are reborn! By Kieron Gillen, Brandon Peterson and Greg Land!

Wolverine, Kitty Pryde, the Beast and Iceman fall into the clutches of Krakoa, the Living Island!

Includes material previously published in Wolverine & The X-Men #3 and Uncanny X-Men #4-6.

Odysseus, one of the great Greek warriors of the Trojan War, has not arrived home. His ship is blown off course by the vengeful sea god Poseidon, thus leading the hero into a series of awesome adventures that form a cornerstone of Western literature.

This Homeric epic has been told and retold and now it receives the grand Marvel Illustrated treatment courtesy of classic scribe Roy Thomas (The Iliad) and penciler Greg Tocchini (Thor: Son of Asgard). It's the greatest voyage in all mythology!

Collects Marvel Illustrated: The Odyssey #1-8.

description: Ready, Set, GO! While on a trip to visit his uncle at a top secret facility known as the Go Base, Jonny Zero is critically injured and his parents killed when their plane is shot out of the sky by a mysterious attacker. Now the only thing that can save Jonny's life will leave him changed forever!

It would seem that Jonny Zero's life had come to an end when his family's plane was shot out of the sky by the evil genius The Cultist. But with an injection of robotic nanoplasm he was both saved and transformed ?into GO BOY 7! Now The Cultist wants to complete the job that he started and has brought to life the very wreckage of the plane that once carried Jonny and his family. Can Jonny defeat the hulking wreckage monster, save the Go Base, AND come to grips with his new super-powered life all at the same time?!

When a top secret spy satellite starts to behave eraticlly and endangers the human population on the Earth below, Go Boy 7 and Jett Girl are sent to investigate. But they might be in for more than they expect when it's discovered that the evil hand of THE CULTIST is involved in rouge satellite's destructive behavior. Don't miss out on a space adventure that will leave you screaming?GO, GO BOY! GO!

Go Boy 7's grief over his murdered parents fuels the Cultist's cruelest bid yet to destroy him! But it's a mistake to make the Jonny too angry, as the Cultist learns when the Human Action Machine tracks him down to his lair! Plus: Jonny learns a terrible secret Professor Zero has been keeping from him!

When Jonny Zero's blood was infused with life saving nanotech plasm his life was changed forever. No longer a simple teenaged boy, Jonny became GO BOY 7-Human Action Machine! Now Jonny's life is one adventure after another as he joins Jett Girl and the rest of the robotic Go Boys on dangerous adventures to help fight the evil of THE CULTIST who seeks the destruction of logic, reason, AND Go Boy 7!
Raggedy Ann & Andy appear on the cover only
